## Enforcement Rules

1. **MANDATORY**: All diagrams must be Mermaid syntax
2. **MANDATORY**: All tags must be `#CONTEXT-REFERENCE` format (PascalCase)
3. **MANDATORY**: All permanent notes must be atomic (200-300 words exactly)
4. **MANDATORY**: All permanent notes must have declarative titles (e.g., "HTTP-methods-define-request-semantics")
5. **MANDATORY**: All permanent notes must declare prerequisites with WikiLinks
6. **MANDATORY**: All permanent notes must have minimum 3 tags, maximum 7 tags
7. **MANDATORY**: All contexts must have dedicated folders in `10-CONTEXTS/`
8. **MANDATORY**: All study plans must include Mermaid dependency diagrams
9. **MANDATORY**: All file names must follow naming conventions (declarative titles for permanent notes)
10. **MANDATORY**: All notes must support Graph View navigation (no orphaned notes)
11. **MANDATORY**: `.obsidian/` directory must be copied to vault root
12. **MANDATORY**: Templates must be placed in `40-RESOURCES/templates/`
13. **MANDATORY**: All internal links must use WikiLinks format `[[note-title]]`, never markdown links
14. **MANDATORY**: Master Index and Context Map must be updated for each new context
15. **MANDATORY**: All permanent notes must include frontmatter with type, context, and tags

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

1. âŒ **Non-atomic notes**: Notes covering multiple concepts - SPLIT into separate notes
2. âŒ **Vague titles**: "Introduction to X" - USE declarative statements instead
3. âŒ **Missing prerequisites**: Notes without prerequisite links - ALWAYS declare dependencies
4. âŒ **Tag overload**: More than 7 tags per note - KEEP focused and relevant
5. âŒ **Orphaned notes**: Notes with no links in/out - CONNECT to knowledge graph
6. âŒ **Non-Mermaid diagrams**: Images or other formats - USE Mermaid exclusively
7. âŒ **Wrong link format**: `[text](link)` - USE `[[wikilink]]` format
8. âŒ **Missing context folder**: Notes outside `10-CONTEXTS/[Context-Name]/` - ORGANIZE properly
9. âŒ **Incomplete index**: New context not in Master Index - UPDATE always
10. âŒ **Generic tags**: `#programming`, `#learning` - USE specific `#Context-Reference` format
